body: Can you reproduce in a separate repo? Stubs should definitely inform property types.
@simPod do you load stubs with `<stub>` in your `psalm.xml`?
Then Psalm has no idea they exist.
@weirdan is there some exclusion for RdKafka namespace so autoloading does not work for those stubs?

None that I know of, I believe it's the case for all stubs. As far as I'm aware there's only two ways to load stub files:
1. Reference them in config
2. Register them `RegistrationInterface::addStubFile()`
@weirdan but these are not typical stubs, this is valid code that lives in vendor. It would work out of the box of it wasn't for psalm overwriting it.

Psalm is not overwriting anything, it just ignores unreachable code. 

> autoloading does not work for those stubs?

These classes are not autoloadable (there's no `autoload` entry in `composer.json`).

That package exploits buggy behavior of some IDEs that ignore autoload definitions and assume any class under project root is available. To make it work with Psalm there's two ways I mentioned earlier.

If you decide to use plugin approach here's the repo you can fork and tweak: https://github.com/weirdan/psalm-plugin-rdkafka

Perhaps it could also be merged upstream, converting `kwn/php-rdkafka-stubs` into Psalm plugin - if they are willing to accept such PR.

Demo: 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/57403/82265342-6c8fbb80-996f-11ea-9d39-8fe2b99f7d08.png)

> These classes are not autoloadable (there's no autoload entry in composer.json).

daym, now it makes sense. Thanks for taking time. Would you register it to Packagist?

> Would you register it to Packagist?

No, I do not intend to support it, as I don't use kafka. Feel free to fork and use however you see fit - including publishing.

To answer your original question, you cannot type the property in CallMap, but there's PropertyMap for that: https://github.com/vimeo/psalm/blob/master/src/Psalm/Internal/PropertyMap.php
